<TEXT>
libyan leader moammar gadhafi on sunday 
threatened to throw his forces into the battle against 
antigovernment rebels in sudan unless the rebels end their revolt 
within a year 
gadhafi said he would attempt to persuade rebel leader john 
garang whose rebellion gadhafi supported in the past to suspend 
his sevenyear fight now that sudan has proposed adopting a 
libyanstyle government 
but gadhafi said libya will have no option but to stand by the 
sudanese people and government against garang if a ceasefire is 
not reached by oct 21 1991 
the rebels operating in southern sudan mostly christians and 
members of traditional african religions are seeking economic and 
political reforms from the moslemdominated government and greater 
autonomy for three southern sudanese provinces 
gadhafis comments were made during the closing session of a 
sixweek conference that recommended sudan copy libyas 
jamaheriya or republic of the masses system of local 
and provincial councils instead of elected officials 
military ruler lt gen omar hassan elbashir who led a coup 
last year to oust a civilian government is expected to ratify the 
recommendations by the 1000member conference 
gadhafi a principal advocate of a panarab state said libya 
sudan and egypt should forge a political and social union 
sudan egypt and libya constitute the heart the main body of 
the arab nation the movement of which control the movement of the 
other arab states said gadhafi whose speech was televised 
throughout sudan 
egypt which follows a parliamentary system has rebuffed 
gadhafis earlier calls for unity 
gadhafi has unsuccessfully attempted to unify libya with most 
arab nations since taking power in 1969 he said peaceful rallies 
would be staged in all arab countries beginning jan 1 to support 
panarab unity 
libya has had close relations with sudan since a 1985 uprising 
that overthrew the prous president gaafar nimeiri elbashir 
banned political parties and dismissed the elected parliament 
gadhafi admitted libya trained and armed the rebel peoples 
liberation army but said he stopped assistance after nimeiris 
ouster 
</TEXT>
