<TEXT>
after taking a back seat to worries about 
taxes the economy and the middle east abortion is reemerging as 
a potentially decisive issue in the final days of the 1990 election 
season 
its one of the few issues thats still out there that 
distinguishes people said harrison hickman a pollster for 
abortionrights causes i would predict youll see a lot of 
people using it at the last minute to try to push undecided 
voters 
conventional political wisdom has held that abortionrights 
candidates had the upper hand this year and that opponents of 
abortion were on the defensive after a 1989 supreme court ruling 
revived the issue electoral losses for abortion foes in 1989 
contributed to that view 
yet abortion hasnt proven to be the silver bullet for 
abortionrights candidates in the words of democrat donald 
avenson a prochoice candidate for iowa governor and abortion 
opponents point to races where their candidates have stood firm and 
are leading including governors races in ohio pennsylvania 
texas and iowa 
its not the issue some thought a year ago on the other hand 
its more salient this year than it has been in the past in a lot 
of states said doug johnson legislative director for the 
national right to life committee 
as a result some thought abortion was fizzling this year as an 
issue 
but strategists for abortionrights campaigns say there will be 
a flurry of lastminute advertising pushing the abortion issue in 
some races its already begun 
sometimes the push will be on television but in other cases it 
will be more selectively targeted toward young women voters through 
directmail or telephone 
people are thinking this is a dead issue i think thats just 
a fundamental misunderstanding of this issue said celinda lake 
who has conducted polling for abortionrights candidates around the 
country 
its a lastminute issue she said its something you lay 
out in the last weeks of a campaign 
abortionrights strategists say their target audience younger 
voters typically does not pay attention to campaigns until the 
final stages 
lake says polling shows that increasing economic worries and 
lack of trust of democrats on the economy has caused a dropoff in 
support for democrats among younger women she said abortion may 
lure them back 
its a big drop off 10 points she said because of that 
youll see more prochoice directmail geared toward that audience 
at the end 
in north carolinas senate race both antiabortion sen jesse 
helms and his democratic challenger harvey gantt have been airing 
ads on the issue 
but in most states its the abortionrights candidates who have 
been using the issue in television ads 
in oregon democrat harry lonsdale has drawn even in his 
challenge to gop sen mark hatfield according to recent polls 
after airing ads that attack hatfields opposition to abortion 
among other issues 
one race where abortion hasnt been the factor that was expected 
is in florida where former sen lawton chiles is challenging gop 
gov robert martinez who opposes abortion chiles who supports 
abortion rights has found the issue uncomfortable for him and 
isnt airing ads despite martinez seeming vulnerability on the 
issue 
the issue is important in iowas senate race where democratic 
incumbent tom harkin has a doubledigit lead over antiabortion 
challenger rep tom tauke according to recent polls 
harkin has been the abortionrights pointman in the senate and 
he led the fight last week to oppose an amendment requiring 
teenage girls to notify their parents before getting an abortion 
parental consent on abortion tends to gain strong support in most 
polls but harkin said the overall abortion issue helps him 
the last thing my opponent wants to talk about is the choice 
issue harkin said im watching my tracking polls and the 
number of people viewing his position as extreme is going like 
this he added pointing upward 
the senate adopted the parental consent provision on a 4848 
vote but the amendment was expected to be deleted in later 
congressional action harkins side was surprised it drew 48 votes 
that vote has become an issue in california where both 
candidates for governor are trying to appeal to abortionrights 
supporters democratic candidate dianne feinstein blasted her gop 
rival sen pete wilson for missing the vote while campaigning 
abortion opponents have the upper hand in several races 
in kansas democratic gubernatorial candidate joan finney has 
had difficulty explaining her antiabortion position recently but 
she still leads gop gov mike hayden an abortionrights supporter 
in the polls 
antiabortion republican george voinovich has the lead in ohios 
governor race where democrat anthony celebrezze has been 
criticized for a startling flipflop in which he dropped his 
longstanding opposition to abortion 
a september poll by the university of cincinnati found that the 
issue was helping voinovich more than celebrezze voinovich led 
among the 13 percent of respondents who said abortion was the 
single most important issue 
in iowas governors race democrat avenson is running 
abortionrights ads but has yet to catch up with antiabortion gop 
incumbent terry branstad 
abortion opponents in idaho were angered by gov cecil andrus 
veto of a restrictive abortion bill this year but he is in strong 
shape in his reelection bid 
its become more of an issue in idahos senate and house races 
however 
idaho republican senate candidate larry craig surprised his 
antiabortion supporters when he was asked in a debate what he 
would do if his wife became pregnant as a result of rape 
he responded that it was her decision which seemed at odds with 
his opposition to legal abortions democrat ron twilegar jumped on 
the response saying he wanted all women to have that choice but 
craig seemed to want it only for his wife craig says he was 
misinterpreted and hasnt strayed from his opposition to abortion 
abortion also is an issue in about a dozen congressional races 
in northern virginia for example democrat james moran is 
airing abortionrights ads against gop rep stan parris 
democrats see the issue helping moran the alexandria mayor 
since the district was won by gov doug wilder in an important 
abortion test last year 
