sen warren rudman was wearing a big smile and 
he didnt mind showing a guest the reason why 
walking to a tall window in his senate office the new hampshire 
republican pointed to the unremarkable looking uhaul parked on the 
street below 
see that truck he said thats davids belongings his 
buddies in new hampshire said well load it up for you and send 
it down and there it is 
david of course is david souter the newest supreme court 
justice as souters longtime friend and mentor rudman suggested 
that president bush nominate him then guided the protege through 
his senate confirmation 
but more than pride was behind that smile there was relief the 
truck was evidence rudman was at last losing the houseguest hed 
put up since the nation was introduced to david souter on july 23 
and he could use the break rudman 60 a likeable secondterm 
senator has found himself caught in a swirl of major battles 
besides shepherding souter through the senate hes been near 
the center of budget debates that bear his name and hes the top 
republican on the senate ethics committee that is weighing the fate 
of five senators involvement in the savingsandloan scandals a 
decision with enormous political potential 
im just on the thin edge rudman said its been an 
unbelievable time im ready to just go on top of a mountain in a 
log cabin thats what im ready for 
its been a very intensive satisfying in many ways three 
months he added in some ways its been very unsatisfying 
rudman a moderate republican was swept into office with ronald 
reagan in 1980 
he unseated democratic sen john durkin who four years earlier 
had blocked president fords appointment of rudman to a top agency 
post rudman won the gop nomination over a wide field that included 
john sununu who later became governor and now is bushs chief of 
staff 
rudman is far more affable and far less ideological than sununu 
that souter was rudmans protege and not sununus was of intense 
comfort to many democrats and in no small way eased his 
confirmation 
rudman is jewish and during the confirmation hearings souter 
sought to display his sensitivity on civil rights by mentioning 
their private discussions of the discrimination rudman has felt as 
a result of his religion 
souter and rudman go back more than 20 years when rudman was 
attorney general of new hampshire and souter worked for him few 
brothers are closer rudman says on his office wall are pictures 
chronicling the intertwined careers of rudman and souter and the 
other member of their trio tom rath a new hampshire lawyer and 
republican activist 
it was incredible very satisfying to me rudman said 
after all hes one of my closest friends very very close hes 
someone who i set on his path 20someodd years ago i told him he 
ought to be a judge to watch him being sworn in was just 
enormously satisfying to me 
less satisfying he says is the crisis over the budget 
he is the rudman of grammrudman a law written with sens phil 
gramm of texas and ernest hollings of south carolina that is the 
nations shorthand for budget crisis 
the law imposed the deadline for deficitcutting that has 
triggered political brinkmanship and brought the government to 
potential shutdown 
rudman is blunt without being a bully as sununu is often 
called he points to blame within his own party for the deficit 
mess and particularly faults house republicans for refusing to go 
along with new taxes 
i dont meant this to be funny i truly understand the new 
politburo in the soviet union better than i understand the 
republicans in the house of representatives he said i dont 
understand what theyre doing i truly dont understand it 
divided government is bad enough he said when you have a 
divided party within a divided government it is even more 
frustrating 
rudmans background as an attorney general helped earn him the 
unenvied seat on the ethics committee which investigates and 
prosecutes senators caught in scandal or misdeeds 
the panel is now deciding what to do about five senators the 
socalled keating five accused of improperly intervening with 
federal regulators on behalf of charles h keating jr whose sampl 
was near insolvency keating contributed 13 million to the 
senators campaigns or groups affiliated with them 
rudman says he doesnt know when the panel will decide but 
acknowledges the job draws political heat 
oh sure this is still a political institution everything we 
do has some political aspects that relate to it he said up to 
now i cannot say ive seen politics enter into the ethics 
committee well see how this plays out 
