<TEXT>
japanese coast guard boats have turned back two 
taiwanese vessels carrying politicians and athletes toward a group 
of tiny uninhabited islands claimed by both nations officials 
said 
the taiwanese had sought to land the delegation on the islands 
called the senkakus in japan and diaoyutai in taiwan on sunday to 
reinforce their claim to the territory and promote a sports event 
taiwans premier hau peitsun said he was displeased by the 
japanese intervention and stressed that his nation will stand by 
the claim to the islands about 120 miles northeast of taiwans 
capital of taipei 
athletes had planned to plant flags of taiwans nationalist 
chinese government and run a torch relay on the main island before 
returning sunday night they also intended to publicize the annual 
taiwan athletic championships that are scheduled to begin on friday 
in their country 
the premier said the nationalist government would seek 
diplomatic means to solve the 45yearold territorial dispute 
kiyoshi harada of the maritime safety agency japans coast 
guard said the taiwanese vessels entered 12mile territorial 
waters claimed by japan despite warnings from patrol boats and 
helicopters 
he said the two boats turned back about two hours after entering 
the waters harada declined to say how many patrol boats and 
helicopters were involved or give other details of the incident 
in taiwan the fishermens association in suao about 35 miles 
southeast of taipei said a radio message indicated about 12 
japanese vessels and two helicopters interdicted the taiwanese 
boats about seven miles from the islands 
the two boats had set out earlier sunday with a flotilla of 30 
fishing boats 
the islands were claimed by japan in 1895 but the nationalists 
who claim to be chinas legitimate government say the islands came 
under chinese sovereignty in 1945 when japan was defeated in world 
war ii 
the united states took over administration of the islands after 
the war and returned them along with okinawa to japan in 1972 a 
year earlier the communist government in china laid claim to the 
islands 
japans kyodo news service said japan tightened patrols after 
about 300 chinese fishing boats approached the islands in 1978 and 
claimed territorial rights 
the latest dispute followed reports that a japanese rightwing 
political group received government permission to renovate a 
lighthouse on one of the islands hau said last week that the 
nationalists would not tolerate japans occupation of the 
territory 
