<TEXT>
the cincinnati reds completed one of the 
biggest upsets in baseball history saturday night rallying past 
the awesome oakland athletics by 21 and winning the world series 
in four quick games 
the reds who began the season with nine straight victories and 
held first place all year closed it with four wins in a row 
cincinnati saved its best for last finishing off the defending 
world series champions despite losing billy hatcher and eric davis 
with firstinning injuries 
jose rijo allowed just two hits in 8 13 innings retiring the 
final 20 batters he faced before randy myers got the last two 
outs finishing a series in which reds relievers pitched 13 
scoreless innings 
it was rijos second victory over dave stewart and it earned him 
the series mvp award 
for the reds it was their ninth straight world series win a 
streak that started in the days of the big red machine they took 
advantage of stewarts first error of the season and scored in the 
eighth on glenn braggs rbi forceout with the bases loaded and hal 
morris sacrifice fly 
barry larkin tied the score on braggs effort and herm 
winningham ran in for the winning run on morris sacrifice fly 
for the as it was a bitter disappointment they were outhit 
4528 and outscored 228 in the series and the loss marked only 
their second fourgame losing streak of the season 
