<TEXT>
rescue workers have found only one fatality from 
a powerful earthquake that hit northwest china but heavy snowfall 
hampered their search for casualties the central seismology bureau 
said sunday 
at the moment we have one dead and two injured but i believe 
there will be more said li qianghua of the bureau 
the temblor measuring 62 on the richter scale hit central 
gansu province saturday afternoon another quake measuring 51 
struck 32 minutes later 
thirty percent of the buildings in the area collapsed and nearly 
all the others sustained damage making them too dangerous to live 
in li said 
provincial rescue workers arrived in the area during the night 
but were confronted by a heavy snowfall the area is between 6600 
and 9900 feet above sea level li said 
the quakes epicenter was near the tianzhu tibetan autonomous 
county 124 miles northwest of the provincial capital of lanzhou 
and 750 miles west of beijing aftershocks were felt as far away as 
lanzhou 
li said the area was not heavily populated 
a severe earthquake last april hit an area less than 124 miles 
away in neighboring qinghai province killing 126 people 
aftershocks from that quake also were felt in lanzhou 
the richter scale is an openended gauge of the energy released 
by a quake as measured by ground motion recorded on a seismograph 
an earthquake measuring 6 can cause extensive damage in a populated 
area 
