the palestinian uprising against israeli 
occupation has led to increased clashes between jews and arabs in 
jerusalem following are some major incidents of recent years 
 
1989 
feb 7 a curfew is imposed on the jerusalem refugee camp of 
shufat after riots and repeated stoning attacks on cars it is the 
first curfew in jerusalem since the uprising began in december 
1987 
april 10 a palestinian is shot to death and two others are 
wounded as they sit near the jaffa gate entrance to jerusalems old 
city the attack is claimed by a jewish underground group the 
sicarites 
may 2 two elderly israelis are stabbed to death and three 
others wounded by a palestinian at a downtown jerusalem bus stop 
july 6 a palestinian man grabs the wheel of an israeli bus en 
route to jerusalem and plunges it over a ravine killing 16 
passengers most of them israelis the palestinian is jailed for 
life 
dec 30 police break up an arabisraeli human peace chain 
around the old city more than 50 people are injured including an 
italian peace activist who loses an eye 
1990 
april 11 about 150 jewish activists take over a christian 
hostel in the old citys christian quarter sparking several days 
of arab riots in the old walled city an israeli court orders most 
of the jews out until ownership of the hostel is sorted out 
may 28 a bomb explodes in the crowded mahane yahuda market 
killing an israeli and injuring nine others arab cars are stoned 
and photographers beaten up 
