have come under heavy criticism from western environmental 
officials for failing to meet safety standards 
the use of nuclear power is a sensitive issue in germany which 
has a powerful network of antinuclear groups the 1986 chernobyl 
nuclear disaster in the soviet union helped fuel the antinuclear 
movement 
goeke said it would be too expensive to modernize the greifswald 
plant to make it safe and would take nearly two months to shut it 
down 
the greifswald and rheinsberg plants also fail to meet european 
community nuclear safety standards that took effect when the 
germanys united oct 3 
goeke said security inspectors have found that the east german 
plants were not properly maintained and often were poorly 
constructed 
the environment ministers of both germanys had decided in the 
spring to shut down all nuclear power reactors in what was then 
east germany environment minister klaus toepfer informed the 
soviet government of the decision during a visit to moscow just 
after unification 
goeke said the german government had allocated 20 million to 
build an oilfueled heating plant in the greifswald region to make 
up for the loss of power when the reactor is shut down the 
oilfueled plant is scheduled to start operating in middecember 
in june officials shut down part of greifswald because of 
safety problems 
they said the plant management had permitted operation of a 
powerproducing block at the plant even though a leak had been 
discovered in what they called its cleaning system 
the magazine der spiegel reported in january that a nuclear 
accident had narrowly been averted at greifswald in 1976 when fire 
destroyed some electrical cables disabling all but one of 12 
watercooling pumps in one of the plants four powerproducing 
blocks 
the five states on the territory of east germany derive only 10 
percent of their electricity from nuclear power the majority of 
their power plants are fueled by brown coal which has seriously 
polluted much of eastern germany 
clouds of the noxious brown coal emissions also float into 
western germany prompting protests from environmental activitists 
