sarawak 
the twothirds majority won by the ruling coalition is necessary 
to amend the constitution and symbolic as a measure of the prime 
ministers power in the old parliament the coalition held 133 of 
the 177 seats the new one was enlarged by three seats 
voting was not compulsory and turnout of the 79 million voters 
ranged from 60 to 70 percent throughout the country 
fifty thousand police officers were on duty and 25000 on 
standby for election day authorities said no violence was 
reported 
no outdoor rallies or political processions have been allowed in 
malaysia since race riots after the 1969 elections left hundreds 
dead in the streets of kuala lumpur that bloodshed occurred after 
chinese parties made inroads on malay political dominance 
