following is a list of major legislation and 
issues yet to be resolved as congress heads toward adjournment of 
the 101st session 
 
budget and taxes 
the house and senate continue their search for a compromise 
deficitreduction package that can be accepted by president bush 
the government is operating on temporary spending authority that 
expires at midnight wednesday by which time both sides hope to 
have a final agreement 
the two sides continued to exchange proposed tax packages on 
sunday but hit a snag late in the day 
final passage is needed as well on the 13 appropriations bills 
financing government agencies in the new budget year which started 
oct 1 
 
artsobscenity 
an 117 billion appropriations bill that would reinstate strict 
antiobscenity restrictions on the national endowment for the arts 
is pending in the senate the bill would trim the agencys 175 
million budget request by 5 million opponents favor a 
houseapproved proposal to let the courts decide whether federally 
subsidized art works are obscene 
 
