members of a house and senate conference are nearing completion 
on compromise clean air legislation which would be the first major 
rewrite of the federal air pollution law in 13 years 
the conferees tentatively approved provisions sunday to sharply 
reduce pollution that causes acid rain the last major section of 
the 700page bill earlier the conferees tentatively agreed on new 
auto emission requirements to curtail urban smog and on reductions 
in toxic chemical pollution by industry 
several minor issues remained to be worked out by the conferees 
the compromise package also still would have to be approved in both 
the house and senate 
 
child care 
senate leaders and the bush administration have reached 
