administration strongly opposes 
 
keating investigation 
the senate ethics committee is pressing ahead with its 
investigation of senators who assisted charles h keating jr as 
his lincoln savings and loan was sinking toward collapse 
 
civil rights 
the white house says bush will veto the civil rights act of 
1990 which is aimed at overturning the effects of recent supreme 
court decisions reversing some affirmative action programs a veto 
override attempt could take place in congress once bush has acted 
