in pine plains where he owned a golf course and was planning a 
700acre residential development plans for the project were 
stalled last year 
born in greece on july 14 1906 carvels family emigrated to 
the united states when he was 4 years old and settled in new york 
city 
in the 1920s carvel played drums in a dixieland band worked as 
an auto mechanic and drove an icecream truck before opening his 
first icecream store in hartsdale in westchester county 
in the mid1920s carvel developed the first machine for making 
soft ice cream and later sold the machine to store owners 
in 1955 he did the first of his many ads in which he appealed 
to the public in his raspy voice to please visit your local 
carvel store 
he is survived by his wife agnes they had no children winkle 
said funeral arrangments were pending he said 
